.TH "wp_pte" 9 "wp_pte" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wp_pte \- Write-protect a pte
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" wp_pte
.BI "(pte_t *pte "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long end "  ","
.BI "struct mm_walk *walk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pte" 12
Pointer to the pte
.IP "addr" 12
The start of protecting virtual address
.IP "end" 12
The end of protecting virtual address
.IP "walk" 12
pagetable walk callback argument
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The function write-protects a pte and records the range in
virtual address space of touched ptes for efficient range TLB flushes.
